# SAML smoke — copy to repo root `.env` (optional live section only).
# Offline smoke (scripts/saml-smoke.sh) needs no IdP credentials.

# --- Offline (default): no variables required ---

# --- Live sandbox (optional, browser + real IdP tenant) ---
# Set SAML_SMOKE_LIVE=1 and fill the block for your IdP vendor.

# OPENAUTH_SECRET=your-session-secret-at-least-32-chars-long
# OPENAUTH_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000

# Provider id registered in your app (must match samlConfig below)
# SAML_SMOKE_PROVIDER_ID=saml-okta-sandbox

# IdP vendor: okta | azure | google
# SAML_SMOKE_IDP_VENDOR=okta

# From IdP admin (SAML app) — PEM X.509 signing cert (single line or file path)
# SAML_SMOKE_IDP_CERT_PEM=/path/to/idp-signing.pem
# SAML_SMOKE_IDP_CERT_PEM="-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\n...\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----"

# IdP SSO URL (entryPoint)
# SAML_SMOKE_IDP_ENTRY_POINT=https://dev-123456.okta.com/app/myapp/exk.../sso/saml

# IdP entity ID / issuer
# SAML_SMOKE_IDP_ENTITY_ID=http://www.okta.com/exk...

# Azure example:
# SAML_SMOKE_IDP_ENTRY_POINT=https://login.microsoftonline.com/<tenant-id>/saml2
# SAML_SMOKE_IDP_ENTITY_ID=https://sts.windows.net/<tenant-id>/

# Google example:
# SAML_SMOKE_IDP_ENTRY_POINT=https://accounts.google.com/o/saml2/idp?idpid=...
# SAML_SMOKE_IDP_ENTITY_ID=https://accounts.google.com/o/saml2?idpid=...
